            <p>244 West 39<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/>
                New York.<lb/>
                Feb. 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 74<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                Rev. Respected Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Allow me<lb/> to acknowledge with many thanks&#44; the receipt of<lb/> your kind letter of welcome&#33;  A word of en&#45;<lb/>couragement &#91;&#63;&#93; from so tired a<lb/> solider in the good cause as yourself&#44; is best<lb/> calculated to furnish endurance &#38; steadfastness<lb/> to the &#91;&#63;&#93;&#39;s ideal &#91;&#63;&#93;aim.  I trust therefore<lb/> you will allow me from time to time the<lb/> privilege of further correspondence with one<lb/> whom the traditions of my family the &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> of the world&#44; have taught me to look up to as<lb/> a model for the way I should go.<lb/></p>
            <p>With many assurances of deep respect<lb/>
                believe me&#44; Rev. Sir&#44;<lb/>
                Yours vy Truly<lb/>
                F. de Sola Mendes.<lb/></p>
        </body>
